text: Pulaski County is a county located in the central portion of the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2020 census, the population was 9,855. The county seat is Hawkinsville. ==References== Category:1800s establishments in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:1808 establishments in the United States Category:Georgia (U.S. state) counties
